{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01CtUb4TtuSuK2iDTBaHZ9nq","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Second Brain Wiki Configuration\n2\t\n3\tThis file configures the skill for Evan's environment. Edit paths and\n4\tprojects as your work evolves.\n5\t\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t## Paths\n9\t\n10\t| Path | Value | Description |\n11\t|------|-------|-------------|\n12\t| Wiki directory | `~/second-brain/wiki/` | Where wiki pages live |\n13\t| Sources directory | `~/second-brain/sources/` | Raw source files stored here |\n14\t| Inbox directory | `~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/` | Drop files here for processing |\n15\t\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\t## Active Projects\n19\t\n20\tThese are your current projects and areas of focus. The skill uses these\n21\tto find connections when ingesting new content.\n22\t\n23\t- **evaluator-super-agent** — automated prototype quality assessment using persona-driven walkthroughs, 7-dimension rubric scoring, actor/evaluator separation\n24\t- **prototype-creator** — generates clickable prototypes from RFEs, tiered AC classification, Playwright automation\n25\t- **agent-eval-harness** — framework for evaluating AI skill quality, eval.yaml configs, judges, scoring pipelines\n26\t- **ai-sdlc-pipeline** — three-phase pipeline: RFE Creator (WHAT) → Prototype Creator (SHOW) → Strat Creator (HOW)\n27\t- **my-cursor-claw** — personal workspace with 20+ skills, MCP connections, notetaking, automations\n28\t- **decision-kit** — Decision Driven Development toolkit, /strategize, /decide, /journal\n29\t- **automated-usability-testing** — simulated usability testing tool, persona YAML files, evaluate-flow protocol\n30\t- **archie** — UX research agent for the RHOAIUX team\n31\t- **rhoai-prototypes** — RHOAI prototype collection for evaluation\n32\t\n33\t---\n34\t\n35\t## Calendar Integration\n36\t\n37\t| Setting | Value |\n38\t|---------|-------|\n39\t| Calendar name | `primary` |\n40\t| Auto-ingest meetings | `true` |\n41\t| Minimum meeting duration | `15 min` |\n42\t| Require notes/transcript | `true` |\n43\t| Skip recurring without notes | `true` |\n44\t\n45\tEvents that qualify for auto-ingestion:\n46\t- Have attached meeting notes or a description with substance (not just \"Weekly sync\")\n47\t- Have a linked Google Doc (agenda, transcript, action items)\n48\t- Duration is 15+ minutes\n49\t- Are not recurring meetings that had no notes added\n50\t\n51\t---\n52\t\n53\t## MCP Integrations\n54\t\n55\t| Integration | MCP Server | Used for |\n56\t|-------------|-----------|----------|\n57\t| Google Docs | `user-google-workspace` | Extracting doc content |\n58\t| Google Calendar | `user-google-workspace` | Meeting ingestion |\n59\t| Slack | `project-0-my-cursor-claw-slack` | Channel message ingestion |\n60\t\n61\t---\n62\t\n63\t## Cross-Link Priority\n64\t\n65\tWhen multiple connections exist, prioritize these categories (from the\n66\twiki index):\n67\t\n68\t1. **Red Hat AI-SDLC** — pipeline components, RFE/prototype/strat flow\n69\t2. **Evaluation & Quality** — rubrics, heuristics, eval harness\n70\t3. **Tools & Skills** — decision kit, cursor claw, skill overlays\n71\t4. **Meetings** — meeting notes with action items and decisions\n72\t5. **Standups** — sprint progress and blockers\n73\t6. **Session Logs** — what was built and shipped\n74\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a6cd2b8-e97e-4155-bee0-36a73a1fd425","uuid":"4ec30433-c087-4b03-8035-eb72785f6370","timestamp":"2026-07-09T16:06:11.333Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/private/var/folders/kd/9pjy5r0x63g010533l28y0cc0000gn/T/agent-eval/2026-07-09-opus-v1/cases/ingest-slack-thread/.claude/skills/second-brain-wiki/references/config.md","content":"# Second Brain Wiki Configuration\n\nThis file configures the skill for Evan's environment. Edit paths and\nprojects as your work evolves.\n\n---\n\n## Paths\n\n| Path | Value | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| Wiki directory | `~/second-brain/wiki/` | Where wiki pages live |\n| Sources directory | `~/second-brain/sources/` | Raw source files stored here |\n| Inbox directory | `~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/` | Drop files here for processing |\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\nThese are your current projects and areas of focus. The skill uses these\nto find connections when ingesting new content.\n\n- **evaluator-super-agent** — automated prototype quality assessment using persona-driven walkthroughs, 7-dimension rubric scoring, actor/evaluator separation\n- **prototype-creator** — generates clickable prototypes from RFEs, tiered AC classification, Playwright automation\n- **agent-eval-harness** — framework for evaluating AI skill quality, eval.yaml configs, judges, scoring pipelines\n- **ai-sdlc-pipeline** — three-phase pipeline: RFE Creator (WHAT) → Prototype Creator (SHOW) → Strat Creator (HOW)\n- **my-cursor-claw** — personal workspace with 20+ skills, MCP connections, notetaking, automations\n- **decision-kit** — Decision Driven Development toolkit, /strategize, /decide, /journal\n- **automated-usability-testing** — simulated usability testing tool, persona YAML files, evaluate-flow protocol\n- **archie** — UX research agent for the RHOAIUX team\n- **rhoai-prototypes** — RHOAI prototype collection for evaluation\n\n---\n\n## Calendar Integration\n\n| Setting | Value |\n|---------|-------|\n| Calendar name | `primary` |\n| Auto-ingest meetings | `true` |\n| Minimum meeting duration | `15 min` |\n| Require notes/transcript | `true` |\n| Skip recurring without notes | `true` |\n\nEvents that qualify for auto-ingestion:\n- Have attached meeting notes or a description with substance (not just \"Weekly sync\")\n- Have a linked Google Doc (agenda, transcript, action items)\n- Duration is 15+ minutes\n- Are not recurring meetings that had no notes added\n\n---\n\n## MCP Integrations\n\n| Integration | MCP Server | Used for |\n|-------------|-----------|----------|\n| Google Docs | `user-google-workspace` | Extracting doc content |\n| Google Calendar | `user-google-workspace` | Meeting ingestion |\n| Slack | `project-0-my-cursor-claw-slack` | Channel message ingestion |\n\n---\n\n## Cross-Link Priority\n\nWhen multiple connections exist, prioritize these categories (from the\nwiki index):\n\n1. **Red Hat AI-SDLC** — pipeline components, RFE/prototype/strat flow\n2. **Evaluation & Quality** — rubrics, heuristics, eval harness\n3. **Tools & Skills** — decision kit, cursor claw, skill overlays\n4. **Meetings** — meeting notes with action items and decisions\n5. **Standups** — sprint progress and blockers\n6. **Session Logs** — what was built and shipped\n","numLines":74,"startLine":1,"totalLines":74}}}
