{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01DML212eeaUbLdXkGcd3P7L","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# AI Helpers Repo Strategy Update — 2026-07-02\n2\t\n3\tAndy Braren's #uxd-rhoai Slack update confirming skill directory structure, independent versioning, and eval config policy for the centralized AI helpers repo.\n4\t\n5\t## Key Points\n6\t\n7\t- Centralized repo distributes skills to consuming projects via merge requests (MRs), not ad-hoc downloads\n8\t- Each skill lives in its own directory with a `SKILL.md` and a `references/` folder — fully self-contained\n9\t- Teams pull only the skills they need; independent versioning per skill directory\n10\t- Review process required for all new skills entering the repo\n11\t- Eval configs (`eval.yaml`) are **recommended-but-optional** now; will become **required** once enough good examples exist\n12\t- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) pattern identified as the right testing approach for skills\n13\t- Andy plans to send a more detailed proposal the following week (2026-07-08)\n14\t\n15\t## Related\n16\t\n17\t- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — the earlier strategy meeting that established centralized repo distribution; this thread is a follow-up confirmation\n18\t- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — the eval framework called out as the testing pattern for skills\n19\t- [WG: UXD Efficiency — 2026-06-29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — AI helpers repo as primary vetted skills source, discussed the week before this thread\n20\t- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — example of a personal skills workspace that follows the self-contained skill directory pattern\n21\t\n22\t## Sources\n23\t\n24\t- ~/second-brain/sources/2026-07-02-uxd-rhoai-ai-helpers-slack.md\n25\t- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n26\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a6cd2b8-e97e-4155-bee0-36a73a1fd425","uuid":"e9570327-57fd-44e7-a8d4-4ca275839d46","timestamp":"2026-07-09T16:06:31.671Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/ai-helpers-repo-slack-2026-07-02.md","content":"# AI Helpers Repo Strategy Update — 2026-07-02\n\nAndy Braren's #uxd-rhoai Slack update confirming skill directory structure, independent versioning, and eval config policy for the centralized AI helpers repo.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- Centralized repo distributes skills to consuming projects via merge requests (MRs), not ad-hoc downloads\n- Each skill lives in its own directory with a `SKILL.md` and a `references/` folder — fully self-contained\n- Teams pull only the skills they need; independent versioning per skill directory\n- Review process required for all new skills entering the repo\n- Eval configs (`eval.yaml`) are **recommended-but-optional** now; will become **required** once enough good examples exist\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) pattern identified as the right testing approach for skills\n- Andy plans to send a more detailed proposal the following week (2026-07-08)\n\n## Related\n\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — the earlier strategy meeting that established centralized repo distribution; this thread is a follow-up confirmation\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — the eval framework called out as the testing pattern for skills\n- [WG: UXD Efficiency — 2026-06-29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — AI helpers repo as primary vetted skills source, discussed the week before this thread\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — example of a personal skills workspace that follows the self-contained skill directory pattern\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/second-brain/sources/2026-07-02-uxd-rhoai-ai-helpers-slack.md\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n","numLines":26,"startLine":1,"totalLines":26}}}
