e workstreams mapped to benefits, pipeline extension diagram, and direct connections to the evaluator super agent's outcome-level awareness requirement.\n\n**Cross-linked with:** ai-sdlc-pipeline.md (added outcomes as upstream step in flow diagram), prototype-creator.md (added Workstream 2 E2E validation link), evaluator-super-agent.md (added outcome-level awareness connection), rfe-creator.md (added Workstream 1 pattern reuse link)\n\n**Category:** Red Hat AI-SDLC\n\n## 2026-06-15 — Session Log\n\n**Sessions:** 4 agent conversations\n\n**Created:** session-log-2026-06-15.md — Built work-context, meeting-prep, standup-writer, and session-log skills; created sprint-manager; crafted prototype-evaluate Slack response; updated internship progress doc.\n\n**Tags:** #daily-log #2026-06-15 #skills #canvas #second-brain #prototype-creator\n\n**Files created/modified:** 8 files across 5 skills, 1 canvas, 1 script\n\n**Cross-linked with:** my-cursor-claw.md, prototype-creator.md, agent-eval-harness.md, evaluator-super-agent.md\n\n**Category:** Session Logs\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Session Log\n\n**Sessions:** 4 agent conversations\n\n**Signal:** 2 important items, 0 stale carry-forwards\n\n**Created:** session-log-2026-06-16.md — Shipped second brain smart check-ins (importance scoring, carry-forward, auto-resolve); created critique, humanize-text, doc-sync, superpowers, trend-scan skills; GitHub README redesign research.\n\n**Tags:** #daily-log #2026-06-16 #zack #shipped #skills #second-brain #github\n\n**Files created/modified:** 7 files across 6 skills, 1 config\n\n**Cross-linked with:** my-cursor-claw.md, decision-kit.md, agent-eval-harness.md\n\n**Category:** Session Logs\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Ingested: Red Hat AI-First Lessons (Jeremy Eder)\n\n**Source:** ~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/redhat-ai-first-lessons v2.pdf — 38-slide deck on agentic SDLC, issue-to-PR bots, eval infrastructure, AgentReady, and organizational change.\n\n**Created:** redhat-ai-first-lessons.md — Comprehensi